## 6. Features

### Feature Set 1: Core Analysis

**F1.1 — Screenshot Submission**  
Users can submit content for analysis by selecting images from their photo library or capturing directly with the camera. The submission flow is the primary action of the application and must be accessible from every major screen.

**F1.2 — Analysis Pipeline Status**  
The application communicates the analysis pipeline state clearly: submitted, processing, complete, or failed. Each state is visually distinct and actionable.

**F1.3 — Threat Results Display**  
Analysis results are presented with a primary verdict (safe, suspicious, dangerous), a threat score, a list of flagged indicators, contextual explanations, and a recommended action.

---

### Feature Set 2: History and Reference

**F2.1 — Analysis History**  
A chronological list of the user's past submissions and their results. Each entry shows the submitted thumbnail, the verdict, and the date. Tapping opens the full result.

**F2.2 — History Management**  
Users can delete individual entries or clear all history. History is stored locally with reference identifiers that can be used to re-fetch results if needed.

---

### Feature Set 3: Onboarding

**F3.1 — First Launch Onboarding**  
A short, illustrated onboarding experience (3 screens maximum) that communicates the core value proposition and primary usage pattern. Skippable for returning users.

**F3.2 — Contextual Permission Prompts**  
Photo library and camera permissions are requested contextually — at the moment the user initiates a relevant action — with a clear explanation of why the permission is needed.

---

### Feature Set 4: Settings and Privacy

**F4.1 — Privacy Transparency Screen**  
A dedicated screen explaining what data is submitted to the backend, how long it is retained, and how it is used. No technical jargon; plain language only.

**F4.2 — Data Management**  
Users can delete all locally stored history and, via a confirmed action, request deletion of their submitted data from the backend.

**F4.3 — Notification Management**  
Users can enable or disable notifications related to analysis completion and security tips. This is optional and off by default.

**F4.4 — Accessibility Settings**  
The app respects system accessibility settings and provides no additional application-level overrides. All system-level settings (Dynamic Type, Bold Text, High Contrast, Reduce Motion) are fully supported.

---

### Feature Set 5: Informational

**F5.1 — Scam Education Content**  
Contextual educational content appears on the results screen, explaining the type of scam detected and general patterns to watch for. This is presented as supplementary information, never blocking the primary result.

**F5.2 — Recommended Actions**  
Each result includes a curated set of recommended next steps appropriate to the threat level. Examples: "Do not click any links," "Contact your bank directly," "Report this message to [relevant authority]."

