## 7. Functional Requirements

### Submission

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| FR-01 | The application must support image submission from the iOS photo library (PHPickerViewController). |
| FR-02 | The application must support image capture from the device camera. |
| FR-03 | Submitted images must be compressed to a maximum file size defined by the backend contract before transmission. |
| FR-04 | The application must display a loading state while an image is being submitted and analyzed. |
| FR-05 | If submission fails, the application must present a retry mechanism without requiring the user to re-select the image. |
| FR-06 | The application must not submit duplicate identical images within a configurable cooldown window. |
| FR-07 | The application must validate that a selected file is a supported image type before submission. |
| FR-08 | The application must provide upload progress feedback for large images. |

### Results

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| FR-09 | The application must display a primary verdict label corresponding to a threat classification received from the backend. |
| FR-10 | The application must display a numeric or visual threat score in a human-readable format. |
| FR-11 | The application must display a list of flagged indicators returned by the backend. |
| FR-12 | Each flagged indicator must include a human-readable description. |
| FR-13 | The application must display at least one recommended action appropriate to the threat level. |
| FR-14 | The application must store the result locally in history upon successful analysis completion. |
| FR-15 | The application must allow the user to share a result summary via the iOS share sheet. |

### History

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| FR-16 | The application must maintain a local history of past analyses with thumbnail, verdict, date, and result reference. |
| FR-17 | History must persist across application launches using local storage. |
| FR-18 | The application must allow individual deletion of history entries. |
| FR-19 | The application must allow bulk deletion of all history entries. |
| FR-20 | Tapping a history entry must navigate to a result detail screen for that analysis. |

### Error Handling

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| FR-21 | The application must detect network unavailability before submission and present an appropriate offline state. |
| FR-22 | The application must handle backend timeout and present a clear user-facing error with retry action. |
| FR-23 | The application must handle backend error responses with appropriate messaging mapped to error categories. |
| FR-24 | The application must never show raw error codes or technical stack information to the user. |
| FR-25 | The application must log errors to a local diagnostic buffer for debugging purposes. |

### Permissions

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| FR-26 | The application must request photo library access only at the point of first submission attempt. |
| FR-27 | The application must request camera access only when the user elects to use the camera capture flow. |
| FR-28 | The application must handle permission denial gracefully, presenting a settings redirect prompt. |
| FR-29 | The application must re-check permission status on each submission attempt and respond accordingly. |

