| NFR-11 | Authentication tokens and sensitive identifiers must be stored in the iOS Keychain, never in UserDefaults or unprotected storage. |
| NFR-12 | The application must not log sensitive user data (image content, analysis results) to any external logging service. |
| NFR-13 | The application must be hardened against common iOS attack vectors relevant to its data handling scope. |

### Accessibility

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-14 | The application must conform to WCAG 2.1 Level AA for all interactive elements. |
| NFR-15 | All interactive elements must have VoiceOver-compatible accessibility labels and hints. |
| NFR-16 | The application must support Dynamic Type across all text elements. |
| NFR-17 | The application must respect the Reduce Motion system preference. |
| NFR-18 | Color must never be the sole differentiator for threat severity — shape, label, and iconography must supplement color. |
