### Maintainability

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-20 | The codebase must be structured such that a new feature can be added in isolation without modifying existing modules. |
| NFR-21 | All business logic must be unit-testable without UI or network dependencies. |
| NFR-22 | The application must support a remote feature flag mechanism to enable or disable features without a release. |

### Privacy

| ID | Requirement |
|----|-------------|
| NFR-23 | The application must not collect device identifiers beyond a randomly generated, non-resettable session token for analysis correlation. |
| NFR-24 | The application must comply with Apple's App Privacy requirements and provide an accurate App Privacy Nutrition Label. |
| NFR-25 | The application must not use any third-party advertising SDKs. |

